I have spent too much time with my best friend discussing wild boar-fighting strategies when you take into account the fact that we have never fought a wild boar.

Yes, our plan is making the beast slam into a large tree by jumping in the last second and then pushing its side.

A male wild boar weighs ~80 kilos, less than me, I can tip it to its side. If it gets concussed I'm pretty sure I would be able to kill it with a sharp large stone.

Plenty of jackals around though, they can be surprisingly dangerous in packs, only a tree can save you.
